    "description": "<p>You can magically move the target and have two options:</p><ul><li><p><strong>Push/Pull</strong>: <strong><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">SPI SPELL TEST</span></strong> vs. <strong><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">STABILITY</span></strong>. On success: move the target 2 * <strong><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">SPI</span></strong> meters in any direction. On fail: move it 1.5m. Afterwards Spell ends</p></li><li><p><strong>Hover</strong>: <strong><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">SPI SPELL TEST</span></strong> vs. <strong><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">STABILITY</span></strong>. On success: the target hovers in the air and Initially on casting and at the start of your <strong><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">TURN</span></strong> you can move it <strong><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">SPI</span></strong> / 2 meters in any direction. <strong><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">SAVE ENDS</span></strong></p></li></ul><h6>Upcasting the Spell</h6><p>When upcasting the spell, increase the <strong><span style=\"text-decoration:underline\">ARCANA</span></strong> Cost and Spell Difficulty by one and for every increase the maximum object weight is doubled and the range increases by 3m.</p><p>You tap into the kinetic forces and manipulate them around the target.</p>",
